[1] Afghanistan, WPV1 new case - media report
Date: Fri 17 Aug 2018
Source: Xinhua Net [edited]
http://www.xinhuanet.com/english/2018-08/17/c_137397973.htm


A new polio case was detected in Afghanistan's southern province of Kandahar, bringing the total cases to 7 in the [southern part of the] country, an official said Friday [17 Aug 2018]. "The virus affecting an 11-month-old girl was found in [the] Zhuwando Hadiro area of Arghandab district a couple of days ago, after a previously detected [case] in the neighboring Helmand province in late June [2018]," Abdul Shakoor Nasrat, who is in charge of the Kandahar Immunity Vaccination Program, told Xinhua.

With the newly reported case, the polio cases reported in the country's southern zone has reached 7; one in Helmand and the remaining 6 in Kandahar province, bringing the total cases to 10 countrywide [Note: this brings the total number of cases in Afghanistan to 11. - Mod.MPP], the official added.

Earlier this month, Afghanistan Public Health Ministry, with the support of the World Health Organization (WHO) and the United Nations Children's Fund (UNICEF), launched a nationwide 5-day campaign to give immunity vaccination doses to 9.9 million children under the age of 5 years. The ongoing insurgency and conflicts have hindered efforts to stamp out the infectious disease in the mountainous country, as 1.2 million children from areas inaccessible to vaccination teams missed the latest drive.

